## Relay-A4 Automatic Relay Mode Architecture
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both
**Depends on:** Relay-G13, Relay-A1, Chat-A2, Errand-A1

`spawn_relay` is the third orchestration primitive alongside `bring_in` (phase transition) and `dispatch` (errand). It bridges the **chat layer** (Forge) and the **pipeline layer** (Relay) by allowing a chat agent to launch an autonomous background pipeline that runs without further chat involvement.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Chat Layer (Forge)"
        I[Isaac — Advisor]
        I -->|writes goals| SP[Specs]
        I -->|spawn_relay| ST[SpawnRelayTool]
    end
    
    subgraph "Bridge"
        ST -->|returns run_id| FH[Forge Stream Handler]
        FH -->|creates| RE[RunEntry in RunStore]
        FH -->|spawns| DR[RelayDriver]
        FH -->|SSE| FE[Chat Frontend]
    end
    
    subgraph "Pipeline Layer (Relay)"
        DR -->|advance_run| PE[PipelineEngine]
        PE -->|ExecuteStep| AT[AgentTurn]
        AT -->|LLM + tools| PR[Provider]
        AT -->|submit_handoff| PE
        PE -->|WaitForHuman| GW[Gate Wait Loop]
        GW -->|poll| RE
    end
    
    subgraph "Monitoring"
        RE -->|SSE| RV[RelayView]
        RV -->|resolve_gate| PE
    end
```

### Three Orchestration Primitives

| Primitive | Layer | Scope | Chat Pollution | Human Involvement |
|-----------|-------|-------|----------------|-------------------|
| `bring_in` | Forge | Switches chat profession | Handoff note injected | Optional gates |
| `dispatch` | Forge | Isolated errand, master continues | Collapsible errand thread | None |
| `spawn_relay` | **Forge → Relay** | **Full background pipeline** | **One relay card only** | **Gate approval in RelayView** |

### Driver Loop

```
advance_run() → ExecuteStep { step_id, profession_id }
    ↓
build_agent(profession_id) → AgentInstance
build_step_messages(task, previous_handoff, feedback) → Vec<ChatMessage>
    ↓
AgentTurn::run(provider, messages) → TurnResult
    ↓
to_handoff(turn_result) → HandoffDocument
    ↓
submit_handoff(handoff) → AdvanceResult
    ↓
├─ ExecuteStep → loop back to top
├─ WaitForHuman → sleep 2s, poll gate status, loop back
├─ Completed → emit run_completed event, exit
└─ Failed → emit run_failed event, exit
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Driver location | `relay/driver.rs` (separate module) | Keeps pipeline engine pure; driver is an execution layer |
| Gate waiting | Polling loop (not channels) | Simple, no deadlock risk, easy to inspect state |
| Context construction | Initial task + previous handoff render + gate feedback | Gives each agent enough context without full chat history |
| Tool registry per turn | Fresh `ToolRegistry::new()` | Tools are stateless; no need to share across steps |
| Project context | `set_tool_context()` thread-local | Reuses existing specs tool infrastructure |
| Flow selection | `post_discovery` skips chat-done work | Avoids wasting tokens on redundant intake/discover |

